ouTube comments]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/youtube-music/"><ins>YouTube Music</ins></a>对“正在播放”页面的最新重新设计正在推广到各地的 iOS 和 Android 设备。有一项新功能为应用程序带来了额外的社交元素。您现在可以在“正在播放”页面上阅读和发表评论。到目前为止，该选项仅限于播放列表。</p><p>根据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://9to5google.com/2023/08/30/youtube-music-now-playing-redesign-2023-comments/"><em><ins>9to5 Google</ins></em></a>分享的截图，该页面上的一些评论可能可以追溯到几年前。因此，谷歌似乎正在用相关 YouTube 视频的评论填充该部分，无论好坏（ <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/you-tube-users-will-get-a-24-hour-timeout-if-their-toxic-comments-are-removed-134147699.html">可能更糟</a>）。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>更新的设计正在逐步推出，因此您可能不会立即看到它，但商店中还有一些其他变化。封面艺术更大，歌曲标题和艺术家姓名现在位于屏幕左侧。另一件需要注意的关键事情是，现在有一个带有评论按钮的轮播，给曲目点赞或反对，将歌曲保存到播放列表，共享，下载和广播。到目前为止，大多数以前可用的操作都需要额外点击才能访问。这些按钮看起来与您在 YouTube 视频播放器下方看到的按钮非常相似。此外，更多控件应该更容易访问，因为它们位于屏幕底部。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/youtube-musics-now-playing-tab-adds-everyones-least-favorite-feature-youtube-comments-164521304.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/youtube-musics-now-playing-tab-adds-everyones-least-favorite-feature-youtube-comments-164521304.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 48898fe7-e413-4341-a850-99b5a0c02dcb</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 16:45:21 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693499427</ingested><modified> 2023-08-31T16:30:30+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7f4cf110-4034-11ee-bf76-171e641c3b00" width="6000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/7f4cf110-4034-11ee-bf76-171e641c3b00" width="6000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Headphones connected to a mobile phone with the logo of You tube on its screen. (Photo by Nikos Pekiaridis/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Music And Sound Streaming Platforms Stock Photos]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Withings' ScanWatch 2 features a body temperature sensor and improved health tracking]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果您不想要智能手表，但确实想要<em>智能手表</em>，那么 Withings 可能是您的最佳选择。在过去的十年里，它一直在生产优雅的混合手表，在未经训练的人看来，这些手表类似于老式<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-05-withings-move-ecg-price-hands-on.html">瑞士手表</a>。在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/withings-scanwatch-hands-on-ifa-2020-070001875.html">推出 ScanWatch</a>三年后，该公司准备展示其后续产品 ScanWatch 2。同时，它还发布了 ScanWatch Light，这是一个更适合钱包的版本，确实没什么值得大书特书的。</p><p> ScanWatch 2是迭代次数最多的升级，配备了新的温度传感器，可以识别感染的早期迹象。其余传感器都得到了改进，以获得更高的精度和更好的能效，但这仅是硬件方面的事情。唯一的另一个变化是人们可以通过将数据输入手腕来跟踪月经周期。几个月后，它将开始提供预测，但令人惊讶的是，这不能与温度跟踪协同工作。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>乍一看，表壳或表面设计似乎也没有太大变化，这里展示的选项与第一代相同。有 38 毫米或 42 毫米的机身，可选择厚或薄的边框和连接到钢制机身黑色或白色表面的表耳。与以前一样，您可以选择宝石色或深蓝色表面和带玫瑰金款式的表带组合。遗憾的是我们没有同时推出<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/withings-scanwatch-horizon-divers-watch-070020840.html">Horizo​​n 版本</a>（将相同的内部结构放入潜水员表体中），但我相信明年就会推出。</p><p> Withings 辩称，它没有太多可以添加到 ScanWatch 中的功能。几年前，我解释过物理和生物定律可以从手腕监控的数据只有这么多。尽管我可能会因为 ScanWatch 2 缺乏新功能而抱怨它，但这并不是 Withings 的错，它上次的表现如此出色。我们不要忘记它优雅的模拟和数字子表盘、跟踪的深度和质量以及 30 天的电池寿命。更不用说 Health Mate，它仍然是同类产品中卓越的健身追踪平台。</p><p>对经期追踪的关注引起了生活在后罗伊时代美国的用户的担忧，因为这些数据可能会被武器化。 Withings 告诉 Engadget，其客户数据存储在一家法国提供商处，该提供商受欧盟法律的约束。其消费者数据的备份保存在 Google Cloud 上，但这些备份是加密的，Withings 是唯一能够解密它们的实体。然而，这可能不足以阻止通过《云法案》强制移交有关美国公民的数据。</p><p>与此同时，ScanWatch Light 是一款去掉了许多现有功能的 ScanWatch。有基本的活动、睡眠和心率监测，但你失去了心电图、血氧饱和度和温度跟踪工具。硬件也被降级，蓝宝石玻璃晶体被大猩猩玻璃取代，加速度计精度较低。考虑到它们各自的价格，如果可以的话，最好购买打折的第一代 ScanWatch。对我来说，这是一种尝试提供一种低成本模型的尝试，使其价格较高的兄弟看起来不错。</p><p> ScanWatch 2 和 ScanWatch Light 即日起即可预订，预计 10 月份开始发货。 38mm 型号的 ScanWatch 2 起价为 349.95 美元，而较小的 ScanWatch Light 售价为 249.95 美元。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/withings-scanwatch-2-features-a-body-Temperature-sensor-and-improved-health-tracking-160037052.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/withings-scanwatch-2-features-a-body-temperature-sensor-and-improved-health-tracking-160037052.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1c19fabc-356e-40ca-9baf-b2650b90b9a7</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 16:30:37 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693401142</ingested><modified> 2023-08-30T13:12:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="931" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/e458dea0-3ce9-11ee-b75f-8e2bd9ba12a5" width="1552"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="931" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/e458dea0-3ce9-11ee-b75f-8e2bd9ba12a5" width="1552"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Withings]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Image of Withings ScanWatch 2 and ScanWatch Light with bands intertwined on a white background.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Withings ScanWatch 2 and ScanWatch Light]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Shredder’s Revenge gets DLC today]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <em>《忍者神龟：碎纸机的复仇》</em>去年夏天推出时<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-shredders-revenge-review-185022231.html"><ins>出人意料地大受欢迎</ins></a>，为老式 2D 格斗游戏注入了新的活力。现在有一些<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8t7fVFRa2pY"><ins>新的付费 DLC</ins></a>可以吸引玩家回到下水道。 <em>Dimension Shellshock</em>更新于今天发布，带来了新角色和新游戏模式。</p><p>该 DLC <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/usagi-yojimbo-will-be-playable-in-the-upcoming-dlc-for-tmnt-shredders-revenge-183946343.html"><ins>于今年夏天早些时候宣布，</ins></a>但并未透露发布日期，所以今天的发布是一个不错的惊喜。 <em>Dimension Shellshock</em>允许您作为两个新玩家玩整个游戏。其中有来自<em>Usagi Yojimbo 的漫画武士 Miyamoto Usagi，</em>他是海龟们偶尔的朋友，还有前足部族士兵 Karai。这两个角色都拥有独特的动作组合和能量提升。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>至于海龟和它们的同类，DLC 引入了调色板交换以保持新鲜感。您甚至不必购买<em>Dimension Shellshock</em>即可使用此功能，因为免费更新仅包含新颜色。 </p><div id="0a1017ce82ab4dbfa3f81c24fe98640a"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8t7fVFRa2pY?si=6ghdcp4dwDyFLBpy" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p>还有全新的生存模式。这不仅仅是将你的角色锁在充满敌人的竞技场中的重演。相反，它包括许多原始级别，称为维度。这里有一点 Roguelite 元素，玩得越多，收集的水晶就越多。这些水晶可用于购买能量提升、额外生命值等。</p><p> <em>Dimension Shellshock</em>售价 8 美元，需要原版游戏的副本。目前可用于 PC、Nintendo Switch、PlayStation 和 Xbox 游戏机。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-shredders-revenge-gets-dlc-today-161511983.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-shredders-revenge-gets-dlc-today-161511983.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 692ce202-5618-41a6-9d5c-2ab3278c05b9</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 16:15:11 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693497741</ingested><modified> 2023-08-31T16:02:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f911a3e0-4815-11ee-a7fc-d863e34ee7e1" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f911a3e0-4815-11ee-a7fc-d863e34ee7e1" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Dotemu]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A bunch of characters from the roster.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[TMNT DLC]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Starfield review: You will like some of it]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>耐心。 <em>《Starfield》</em>是一款以新有人居住的星球为背景的大型游戏，它将星际旅行与激烈的枪战、外星探索、宇宙飞船管理、角色定制和人际冲突结合在一起，所有这些层次需要一段时间才能融合成一个连贯的内容。经验。但是，给<em>《Starfield》</em>一些时间，优雅地处理它的系统，你将获得一款大型、通用的科幻角色扮演游戏。</p><p> <em>《星空》</em>有美丽的时刻，但它的主要任务线也有很多苦差事和脱节的情况。在 Xbox Series S 上运行预发布代码时，这些问题只会因帧速率突兀、低分辨率设置以及大约每五个小时发生一次严重崩溃而加剧。 <em>《Starfield》</em>很大，而且基本上平淡无奇，虽然它在一些开放世界的游戏玩法方面做得不错，但它并没有为科幻或角色扮演游戏类型提供任何新东西。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f822ed30-480c-11ee-bffd-d113da262186" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f822ed30-480c-11ee-bffd-d113da262186" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="星空" data-uuid="bfeded4b-efe9-3a92-88a2-03a4c2f143b4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">贝塞斯达</div></figure><p>也就是说， <em>《Starfield》</em>中有很多经典的宇宙环境可供享受，并且每个玩家都有可能找到与他们产生共鸣的游戏玩法。 Bethesda 声称需要数百小时才能与<em>Starfield</em>中的所有内容进行交互，我可以说 40 小时和一款 New Game Plus 之后，这感觉不像是谎言。我几乎没有触及一些后期游戏系统的表面，例如前哨建设和深度船舶定制，但我在完成主要故事情节和相关支线任务（包括探索、采矿、社交操纵）时对这些机制有了一定的了解。 、资源管理、制作、烹饪和战斗——无论是在地面还是在星际之间。</p><p>不幸的是，战斗是<em>《Starfield</em> 》的弱点之一。枪战是游戏核心循环的核心，但常常让人觉得没有必要。有些遭遇很简单，但有些遭遇实际上是一个路障，有太多的敌人、机器人和炮塔需要摧毁，没有潜行的机会，而且高级子弹海绵会随机出现。我的建议是注意你正在射击的每个敌人的等级，如果你不知所措，请直接跑过困惑的敌人以解锁任务的下一步。 （这种策略在数量惊人的遭遇战中有效，但感觉从来都不是很好）。</p><p>我对<em>《Starfield</em> 》战斗的问题很大程度上源于它的同质武器。也许我被《无主之地》宠坏了，但<em>《星域》</em>中的枪感觉彼此非常相似，而且通常射击起来并不令人满意。随着时间的推移，这种情况会有所改善——玩家可以选择修改他们的武器库，并且有一些具有元素效果的枪支散布在银河系各处——但总的来说，战斗感觉像是为了安抚 FPS 玩家而附加的东西，尽管它是游戏进程的核心。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f8233b50-480c-11ee-acfe-5f783c28fec0" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f8233b50-480c-11ee-acfe-5f783c28fec0" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="星空" data-uuid="9a8618f6-82f8-3e2e-8315-95ffc576402d"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">贝塞斯达</div></figure><p>这里没有 VATS，只有用于升级统计数据的物品和最终添加到您的装备中的辅助能力树。助推包的触感很好，可以让玩家在不消耗宝贵氧气的情况下短时间飞行。这些功能有助于使战斗更加动态，但即使在主要任务的最后战斗中，枪战也感觉不一致或引人注目。 <em>《Starfield</em> 》的战斗并不糟糕，但体验却非常<em>糟糕</em>。</p><p>对我来说，偷偷摸摸从来都不是一个真正的选择——我在潜行技能上加了分，但即使有蹲伏计，保安和太空海盗也总是会立即发现我，他们都选择了暴力。当然，我可以专注于升级我的隐形树，但我正忙于最大限度地发挥我的说服技能，并在我的船上添加推进器等工具（我建议尽早这样做）。</p><p>感觉重复的不仅仅是<em>《Starfield》</em>中的武器。无论位于哪个星球，建筑物都具有三种风格：明亮的乌托邦、坚韧的赛博朋克和工业实验室。战斗环境往往混合在一起，有金属平台、楼梯和工厂般的基地中的通风口。有时它们被建造在一个极其黑暗的洞穴系统中，但它们通常充满了相同的容器、门和敌人。赛博朋克城市霓虹灯——我打赌你能猜到它是什么样子——本质上是新亚特兰蒂斯地下市场的扩展版本，新亚特兰蒂斯是你的角色的总部。主要商业区在各个星球上都很容易辨认，拥有干净的白色建筑。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f8233b51-480c-11ee-bdef-bd7e2ac6584c" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/f8233b51-480c-11ee-bdef-bd7e2ac6584c" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="星空" data-uuid="61a08c22-8eb2-3ed7-8101-d936a1662729"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">贝塞斯达</div></figure><p>这些场景不仅彼此相似，而且在科幻小说中也是典型的。从视觉角度来看， <em>Starfield</em>并没有提供什么新东西。考虑到游戏的复古未来主义角度，这并不奇怪，它的设计限制了《银翼杀手》、《星际迷航》、《星球大战》和其他非常受欢迎的系列所挖掘的特定美学。除此之外，还错失了构建独特世界的机会——游戏中没有智慧的外星生命，即使是远离地球严格边界的几代人，人类也说着带有明显地区口音的英语。在整个太阳系中，从船只到摩天大楼再到服装， <em>《星空》</em>充满了单调。</p><p>尽管它很熟悉，但我在 Neon 中度过了一段愉快的时光。在塑造我的角色时，我选择将自己与霓虹灯街头的老鼠联系起来，这种特质帮助我在城市的棱镜灯光下感到宾至如归，提供了宝贵的对话选项和见解。到了磨练的时候，我选择把时间花在 Neon 上，为各种公民和商店老板完成任务，并最终在一家大型科技公司找到了一份从事企业间谍活动的工作。任何喜欢贝塞斯达对话树和说服机制的人都会在这里感到高兴，但要注意，战斗也被硬塞到了大多数任务中。</p><p>当我需要从窃取商业机密中休息一下时，我会在主要任务中探索一些行星，跟踪扫描仪上的扭曲，勘察景观并一路增强力量。对我来说，这些是<em>《Starfield》</em>中最平静、最令人愉快的时刻：沿着失落定居点的废墟漫步，简单的钢琴音乐像星际雷达一样回响，音符慢慢构建，挑逗下一个弯道之外的冒险。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/22b8d510-480c-11ee-91f7-3210db365327" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/22b8d510-480c-11ee-91f7-3210db365327" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="星空" data-uuid="d79b2e52-e6a4-3272-bae6-de808de5c8bb"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">恩杰特</div></figure><p>这是我在<em>Starfield</em>中喜欢的循环。其他玩家将会被 Neon 之外的任务所吸引；其他人会花几个小时定制他们的船只、装备和前哨站；有些人会坚持星际战斗并完成他们的星图。尽管总体地形中仍然存在大量的灰色和棕色，但行星上的多样性足以证明探索的合理性。舰船战斗一开始很棘手，但只要你没有突然受到强大敌人的轰炸，它很快就会成为资源管理和目标优先顺序的令人愉快的挑战。</p><p>在<em>Starfield</em>有很多事情可以做，很多事情可以享受。 Digipick 开锁机制非常令人满意，我愿意将其作为独立游戏来玩。主要任务线的结尾引入了一个引人注目的转折，在疯狂的枪战中扰乱了玩家的现实感，这是我在战斗中最有趣的。虽然我很想见到一些外星人，但看到这么多女性、LGBT 人士和有色人种在整个游戏中担任领导职务真是太棒了。</p><p> <em>Starfield</em>是一款经典的 Bethesda RPG，从嘟嘟到鼻涕虫，其中包含一连串的技术问题。我看到了面部和动作动画的问题，遇到了几乎没有意义的对话和说服树，并且与粗鲁地面向错误方向的角色进行了多次对话。</p><p>我在 Xbox Series S 上玩游戏，我将一些额外的故障归咎于该硬件，包括我的游戏在 40 小时内崩溃了 10 次。有大量的自动保存，所以我只失去了两次重大进展，但这比我想要的要频繁。该游戏还存在冗长的静态加载屏幕和一致的帧速率问题。在一个场景中，一个角色正在描述我应该如何潜入竞争对手的总部，而建筑物布局的图像充满了屏幕，像素化得无法辨认。</p><p> “如你所见……”这个角色说道，充分说明了视觉上的侮辱。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/22613f30-480c-11ee-beb6-fd4c44f63af4" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/22613f30-480c-11ee-beb6-fd4c44f63af4" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="星空" data-uuid="21700d68-c4b3-3f05-973a-025218fd2f25"><figcaption> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://mysterio.yahoo.com/api/res/1.2/KW7.RXYNUKzED.0GQRldlA--/ZHByPTI7dz04NzU7YXBwaWQ9ZW5nYWRnZXQ-/https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/22613f30-480c-11ee-beb6-fd4c44f63af4.cf.webp">单击查看全尺寸图像</a></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">恩杰特</div></figure><p><em>《Starfield》</em>中讲述的故事是主流科幻小说，虽然它不是革命性的，但它非常适合角色扮演游戏。它建立了一个可供收集的物品和可获取的知识的世界，一路上不断出现神秘、危险和新角色。当主要叙事被抛到一边时，游戏处于最佳状态，玩家可以自由地在新行星上闲逛，玩他们的宇宙飞船，寻找定居点或只是探索银河系。</p><p> <em>Starfield</em>很大，它包含每个玩家都可以享受的任务或机制 - 他们可能需要玩 40 个小时的游戏，然后才能发现这个循环。贝塞斯达游戏工作室负责人托德·霍华德在给评论者的信中表示，游戏有 300 万字；他注意到了文本的数量，但这个数字并没有说明质量。</p><p>总体来说，<em>星域</em>还是不错的。它是其他科幻游戏和参考文献中的弗兰肯斯坦怪物，并且它在这些方面的表现并不比现有产品更好。战斗？<em>赛博朋克2077</em>更流畅。采矿和勘探？这就是<em>《无人深空》的</em>全部内容。船舶管理？ <em>FTL</em>仍然占据主导地位。 RPG 讲故事？<em>外面的世界</em>就是最好的选择。</p><p>不过，Digipicks 呢？那一个去<em>星域</em>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/starfield-review-you-will-like-some-of-it-160046067.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/starfield-review-you-will-like-some-of-it-160046067.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> d792b9fa-a4d5-46be-a661-7f3384181c76</guid><dc:creator>杰西卡·康迪特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 16:00:46 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693494673</ingested><modified> 2023-08-31T15:11:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="2160" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/228b5c70-480c-11ee-bdb1-b7d48178e84d" width="3840"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2160" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/228b5c70-480c-11ee-bdb1-b7d48178e84d" width="3840"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Bethesda]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Starfield]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Starfield]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Shure's new Aonic 50 headphones have spatial audio and double the battery life]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>舒尔第二代版本的 Aonic 50 耳机的设计可能没有太大改变，但它在内部做了大量的工作，全面升级了性能。该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.shure.com/en-US/products/headphones/aonic50?variant=SBH50G2-BK">今天发布了新型号</a>，这是一套售价 349 美元的高级降噪无线耳机，现在提供空间音频、改进的主动降噪 (ANC) 以及之前版本电池寿命的两倍。</p><p>在音质方面，舒尔表示，新款 Aonic 50 配备了空间音频技术，利用“声学建模和批判性聆听”算法来提供沉浸感，而不会影响原始音频。这里有三种模式——音乐、电影和播客——该公司解释说，这些模式是根据每个用例量身定制的。音乐模式提供“高端扬声器”的聆听体验，而影院模式则添加更多低端音调，给人一种身处剧院的效果，保持清晰度并提供“自然的声音”对话。播客模式使主持人的声音更接近用户的耳朵。这一切均由 50 毫米动态驱动器和带有 aptX Adaptive 的 Snapdragon Sound 提供支持，让您能够以 AAC、SBC 和 LDAC 编解码器传输音乐。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Rather than keep the ANC setup from the previous version, tech simply described as &quot;adjustable,&quot; Shure opted for a new hybrid active noise cancellation system. Like hybrid ANC on other headphones, the company uses microphones on the inside and the outside of the ear cup to monitor environmental clamor. Shure also allows you to control the amount of noise blocking and ambient sound with four modes: Light, Moderate, Max and MaxAware. The last of which is a new option the company describes as &quot;perfect balance between blocking unwanted noise and maintaining awareness of your surroundings.&quot; There&#39;s also an Enhanced Environment mode that allows you to adjust those levels with a slider rather than relying on presets.</p><p> Shure has more than doubled the battery life for the second-gen Aonic 50. It now offers up to 45 hours of listening time on a charge, up from the 20 hours on the previous version. There&#39;s also a quick-charge feature on the new model that gives you five hours of use in 15 minutes. The company is also touting &quot;superior&quot; call quality thanks to beamforming mics with automatic gain control. Shure says the six built-in microphones adjust automatically to combat ambient noise, which it claims provides &quot;unmatched&quot; clarity. Companies make lofty promises about voice performance all the time, and since mileage varies greatly on those, we&#39;ll have to reserve judgement here until we can complete our own testing.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.shure.com/en-US/products/headphones/aonic50?variant=SBH50G2-BK">Aonic 50 (2nd gen)</a> will be available in September.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/shures-new-aonic-50-headphones-have-spatial-audio-and-double-the-battery-life-160025565.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/shures-new-aonic-50-headphones-have-spatial-audio-and-double-the-battery-life-160025565.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7850404e-c954-4b0b-84af-00d7b47dd7ec</guid><dc:creator>比利·斯蒂尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 16:00:25 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693491284</ingested><modified> 2023-08-31T14:14:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/0b17b970-4803-11ee-a98e-98555ba8633e" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/0b17b970-4803-11ee-a98e-98555ba8633e" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Shure]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Shure Aonic 50 (2nd gen)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Shure Aonic 50 (2nd gen)]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Lavoie buys VanMoof, giving the e-bike maker a bankruptcy liferaft]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Just over a month <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vanmoof-e-bikes-has-declared-bankruptcy-094041635.html">after it declared bankruptcy</a> , e-bike maker <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/vanmoof/">VanMoof</a> has found a new home. Lavoie, the electric scooter division of McLaren Applied, has agreed to buy VanMoof and make investments in it to grow the business. According to a press release, Lavoie and its parent plan to &quot;inject stability into the VanMoof operations&quot; before bringing together their &quot;capabilities to create a next-generation e-mobility business and establish a world-leading premium e-mobility offering.&quot;</p><p> Terms of the acquisition haven&#39;t been disclosed, but Lavoie and McLaren Applied appear to have a reasonable understanding of the challenge that lies ahead to get VanMoof back on track. McLaren Applied Chairman Nick Fry told <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/deals/mclaren-applieds-lavoie-buys-bankrupt-dutch-e-bike-maker-vanmoof-2023-08-31/" data-original-link="https://www.reuters.com/markets/deals/mclaren-applieds-lavoie-buys-bankrupt-dutch-e-bike-maker-vanmoof-2023-08-31/"><em>Reuters</em></a> <em>&nbsp;</em> that VanMoof is &quot;a company with a brilliant product&quot; that offers his team an opportunity in a new market, &quot;but this is not going to be a walk in the park. This also is a company that got itself into a difficult financial situation.&quot; Fry noted that McLaren Applied would need to invest &quot;tens of millions&quot; of pounds &quot;in the short term&quot; to stabilize VanMoof.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Lavoie CEO Eliott Wertheimer pointed out that VanMoof has more than 190,000 e-bike customers, some of whom have been <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.theverge.com/23822598/lavoie-buys-vanmoof-e-bikes" data-original-link="https://www.theverge.com/23822598/lavoie-buys-vanmoof-e-bikes">struggling to obtain parts</a> for repairs after production was suspended. Lavoie&#39;s goal is to &quot;continue to keep those riders on the road whilst we stabilize and efficiently grow the VanMoof business and continue to develop its world-class products.” However, there will be layoffs as part of the acquisition. VanMoof will also shift away from an in-house retail store model to instead sell and service bikes via third-party partners. Peloton has <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/peloton-will-sell-its-merchandise-on-amazon-free-delivery-203845216.html">made a similar shift</a> in its business model over the last year or so.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/lavoie-buys-vanmoof-giving-the-e-bike-maker-a-bankruptcy-liferaft-151547609.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/lavoie-buys-vanmoof-giving-the-e-bike-maker-a-bankruptcy-liferaft-151547609.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5c4c8f39-dc15-48ad-80cf-3adebc6829e9</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 15:15:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693494774</ingested><modified> 2023-08-31T15:12:58+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Investment & Company Information]]></category><category><![CDATA[Finance]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-10/10887c60-456f-11ed-9ffd-c4a93c78f8af" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-10/10887c60-456f-11ed-9ffd-c4a93c78f8af" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Mat Smith/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[VanMoof S5 first impressions]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[VanMoof S5 first impressions]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gaming monitors in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Finding the best <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-to-buy-a-monitor-143000069.html">computer monitor</a> for your needs is already hard enough, but as soon as you decide to go for one that&#39;s suited for gaming, there are a ton of additional factors and features to consider. What are refresh rates? What&#39;s the difference between NVIDIA G-Sync and AMD FreeSync? Those are just some of the questions this guide aims to answer, and, in the process, help you find the best gaming monitor for your budget.</p><h2> LCD vs OLED</h2><p> When shopping for a new gaming monitor, you first need to decide if you want to go with a screen that has an LCD or OLED panel. For most people, that choice will come down to price; OLED gaming monitors are significantly more expensive than their LCD counterparts. But even if money isn&#39;t a concern, the choice might not be as straightforward as you think.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> LCD monitors come in three different varieties: twisted nematic (TN), vertical alignment (VA) or in-plane switching (IPS). Without getting too technical, each panel type has its own set of quirks. For the most part, you want to avoid TN monitors unless you&#39;re strapped for cash or want a monitor with the fastest possible refresh rate. TN screens feature the worst viewing angles, contrast ratios and colors of the bunch. After using an IPS monitor for many years and testing an OLED monitor for this guide, I can&#39;t go back to a TN panel.</p><p> The differences between VA and IPS panels are more subtle. Historically, VA gaming monitors have featured slower pixel response times than their TN and IPS counterparts, leading to unsightly image smearing. However, that&#39;s improved in recent years. VA panels also frequently sport better contrast ratios than both TN and IPS screens. They&#39;re not dramatically better than their IPS siblings on that front, but when contrast ratios aren&#39;t an inherent strength of LCDs, every bit helps.</p><p> On the other hand, IPS panels excel at color accuracy and many offer refresh rates and response times that are as fast as the fastest TN panels. The majority of LCD gaming monitors on the market today feature IPS panels, though you will frequently find VA screens on ultrawide monitors.</p><p> In many ways, OLED is the superior display tech. There&#39;s something transformational about the ability of organic light-emitting diodes to produce true blacks. Simply put, every game looks better when there&#39;s no backlight to wash out shadow details. Moreover, if you buy an OLED monitor, you can experience something PC gamers have been missing out on for a while: proper HDR gaming.</p><p> Unfortunately, OLED screens also come with a few noteworthy drawbacks. One big one is text legibility. Almost all OLEDs feature sub-pixel layouts that produce noticeable text fringing in Windows. It&#39;s not an issue you will see when gaming, but it does mean they aren&#39;t the best for productivity.</p><p> Another issue — and everyone&#39;s favorite topic of conversation whenever OLEDs come up — is burn-in. Organic light-emitting diodes can get “stuck” if they display the same image for long periods of time. Every OLED gaming monitor you can buy in 2023 comes with features designed to prevent burn-in and other image retention issues, but those displays haven&#39;t been on the market long enough for us to know how they handle all the static elements that come with Windows. When you consider those drawbacks, OLEDs are great for gaming but they&#39;re less ideal for everyday PC use.</p><h2> Screen size, resolution and aspect ratio </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/18078160-4768-11ee-bf66-3d593d1e21e7" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/18078160-4768-11ee-bf66-3d593d1e21e7" style="height:1067px;width:1600px;" alt="The best gaming monitor" data-uuid="110f7ade-c76f-3b32-b7ed-75709e8e6892"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Igor Bonifacic / Engadget</div></figure><p> After deciding where you fall on the LCD vs OLED debate, you can start thinking about the size of your future gaming monitor. Personal preference and the limitations of your gaming space will play a big part here, but there are also a few technical considerations. I recommend you think about size in conjunction with resolution and aspect ratio.</p><p> A 1440p monitor has 78 percent more pixels than a 1080p screen, and a 4K display has more than twice as many pixels as a QHD panel. As the size of a monitor increases, pixel density decreases unless you also increase resolution. For that reason, there tend to be sweet spots between size and resolution. For instance, I wouldn&#39;t recommend buying a FHD monitor that is larger than 24-inches or a QHD one bigger than 27 inches. Conversely, text and interface elements on a 4K monitor can look tiny without scaling on panels smaller than 32 inches.</p><p> You also need to consider the performance costs of running games at higher resolutions. The latest entry-level GPUs can comfortably run most modern games at 1080p and 60 frames per second. They can even render some competitive titles at 120 frames per second and higher — but push them to run those same games at 1440p and beyond, and you&#39;re bound to run into problems. And as you&#39;ll see in a moment, a consistently high frame rate is vital to getting the most out of the latest gaming monitors.</p><p> If your budget allows for it, 1440p offers the best balance between visual clarity and gaming performance. As for 1080p and 4K, I would only consider the former if you&#39;re on a tight budget or you exclusively play competitive shooters like <em>Valorant</em> and <em>Overwatch 2</em> . For most people, the user experience and productivity benefits of QHD far outweigh the performance gains you get from going with a lower resolution screen.</p><p> Before the end of last year, I would have said 4K was not a viable resolution for PC gaming, but then NVIDIA came out with its <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-rtx-4090-announced-152529456.html">40 series GPUs</a> . With those video cards offering the company&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-dlss-3-ada-lovelace-160404110.html">DLSS 3</a> frame generation technology, there&#39;s a case to be made that the technology is finally there to play 4K games at a reasonable frame rate, particularly if you exclusively play big, AAA single-player games like <em>Control</em> and <em>Cyberpunk 2077</em> or enjoy strategy games like the Total War series. However, even with frame generation, you will need a GPU like the <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://store.nvidia.com/en-us/geforce/store/?page=1&amp;limit=9&amp;locale=en-us&amp;gpu=RTX%204080&amp;category=GPU,DESKTOP">$1,099 RTX 4080</a> or <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://store.nvidia.com/en-us/geforce/store/?page=1&amp;limit=9&amp;locale=en-us&amp;gpu=RTX%204090&amp;category=GPU,DESKTOP">$1,599 RTX 4090</a> to drive a 4K display. Plus, 4K gaming monitors tend to cost more than their 1440p counterparts.</p><p> If you want an OLED monitor, your choices are more limited. It was only at the end of last year that LG <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lg-27gr95qe-us-pricing-availability-announced-181515149.html">began producing 27-inch OLED panels</a> . What&#39;s more, the first batch of 32-inch 4K OLED gaming monitors <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.pcgamer.com/that-4k-32-inch-oled-gaming-monitor-youve-been-waiting-for-will-finally-arrive-in-summer-2024/">won&#39;t arrive until next year</a> . A few companies have <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alienware-qd-oled-gaming-monitor-ultrawide-review-140012704.html">released ultrawide monitors</a> with Samsung QD-OLED panels, but expect to pay a hefty premium for one of those.</p><p> Speaking of ultrawides, note that not every game supports the 21:9 aspect ratio and fewer still support 32:9. When shopping for a curved monitor, a lower Radius, or &#39;R&#39; number, indicates a more aggressive curve. So, a 1000R monitor is more curved than an 1800R one.</p><h2> Refresh rates and response times</h2><p> And now finally for the fun stuff. The entire reason to buy a gaming monitor is for their ability to draw more images than a traditional PC display. As you shop for a new screen, you will see models advertising refresh rates like 120Hz, 240Hz and 360Hz. The higher the refresh rate of a monitor, the more times it can update the image it displays on screen every second, thereby producing a smoother moving image. When it comes to games like <em>Overwatch</em> , <em>Valorant</em> and <em>League of Legends</em> , a faster refresh rate can give you a competitive edge, but even immersive single-player games can benefit.</p><p> A monitor with a 360Hz refresh rate will look better in motion than one with a 240Hz or 120Hz refresh rate, but there are diminishing returns. At 60Hz, the image you see on your monitor is updated every 16.67ms. At 120Hz, 240Hz and 360Hz, the gap between new frames shortens to 8.33ms, 4.17ms and 2.78ms, respectively. Put another way, although a 360Hz monitor can display 50 percent more frames than a 240Hz screen in a given time period, you will only see a speedup of 1.14ms between frame intervals. And all that depends on your GPU&#39;s ability to render a consistent 360 frames per second.</p><p> Ultimately, a fast monitor will do you no good if you don&#39;t have a graphics card that can keep up. For example, with a 1440p 360Hz monitor, you realistically need a GPU like the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-rtx-4070-review-the-new-1440p-gaming-leader-130010874.html">RTX 4070</a> or <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-rtx-4080-review-more-practical-4k-gaming-titan-140009349.html">RTX 4080</a> to saturate that display while playing competitive games like <em>Overwatch 2</em> and <em>Valorant</em> .</p><p> There&#39;s also more to motion clarity than refresh rates alone. Just as important are response times, or the amount of time it takes for pixels to transition from one color to another and then back again. Monitors with slow response times tend to produce smearing that is distracting no matter what kind of game you&#39;re playing. Unfortunately, response times are also one of the more opaque aspects of picking the best gaming monitor for your needs.</p><p> Many manufacturers claim their products feature 1ms gray-to-gray (GtG) response times, yet they don&#39;t handle motion blur to the same standard. One of the reasons for that is that many companies tend to cherry pick GtG results that make their monitors look better on paper. The Video Electronics Standards Association (VESA) recently <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vesa-clearmr-specifcation-announced-190731478.html">created a new certification program</a> to address that problem, but the grading system is unwieldy and, as far as I can tell, hasn&#39;t had a lot of pickup from manufacturers.</p><p> For now, your best bet is to turn to resources like <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.rtings.com/">Rtings</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/@monitorsunboxed">Monitors Unboxed</a> when shopping for a new gaming monitor. Both outlets conduct extensive testing of every screen they review, and present their findings and recommendations in a way that&#39;s easy to understand.</p><h2> FreeSync vs G-Sync </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/2912e8a0-4768-11ee-958f-d84b6872a0c9" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/2912e8a0-4768-11ee-958f-d84b6872a0c9" style="height:1067px;width:1600px;" alt="The best gaming monitor" data-uuid="2a282f26-e954-3f72-8404-250458a7a2df"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Igor Bonifacic / Engadget</div></figure><p> No matter how powerful your system, it will sometimes fail to maintain a consistent framerate. In fact, you should expect frame rate fluctuations when playing graphically-intensive games like <em>Cyberpunk 2077</em> and <em>Control</em> . For those moments, you want a gaming display with adaptive sync. Otherwise, you can run into screen tearing.</p><p> Adaptive sync technologies come in a few flavors. The two you&#39;re most likely to encounter are AMD FreeSync and NVIDIA G-Sync, and each has its own set of performance tiers. With G-Sync, for instance, they are – from lowest to highest – G-Sync Compatible, G-Sync and G-Sync Ultimate.</p><p> The good news is that you don&#39;t need to think too much about which adaptive sync technology a display supports. In the early days of the tech, it was rare to see a gaming monitor that offered both FreeSync and G-Sync, since including the latter meant a manufacturer had to equip their display with a dedicated processor from NVIDIA. That <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-01-07-nvidia-freesync-g-sync-certification.html">changed in 2019</a> when the company introduced its <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:NVIDIA;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f52348f6-2304-415e-b16c-1fb252794066&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=NVIDIA&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfMIIy0hrK7GXTFlosps1DgFd5HomRlrdJOrGa7dbJyL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-us%2Fgeforce%2Fproducts%2Fg-sync-monitors%2Fspecs%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/geforce/products/g-sync-monitors/specs/">G-Sync Compatible certification</a> . In 2023, if a monitor supports FreeSync, it is almost certainly G-Sync Compatible too, meaning you can enjoy tear-free gaming whether you&#39;re using an AMD or NVIDIA GPU.</p><p> In fact, I would go so far as to say you shouldn&#39;t make your purchasing decision based on the level of adaptive sync performance a monitor offers. As of the writing of this guide, the list of G-Sync Ultimate-certified displays is less than two dozen models long, and some are a few years old now.</p><h2> Inputs</h2><p> Almost every gaming display on the market right now comes with at least one DisplayPort 1.4 connection, and that&#39;s the port you will want to use to connect your new monitor to your graphics card. If you own a <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-console-140057674.html">PS5 or Xbox Series X/S</a> , it&#39;s also worth looking out for monitors that come with HDMI 2.1 ports, as those will allow you to get the most out of your current generation console.</p><h2> A word about HDR</h2><p> As fast and responsive gaming monitors have become in recent years, there&#39;s one area where progress has been frustratingly slow: HDR performance. The majority of gaming monitors currently on sale, including most high-end models, only meet VESA&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://displayhdr.org/">DisplayHDR 400</a> certification. As someone who owns one such monitor, let me tell you right now it&#39;s not even worth turning on HDR on those screens. You will only be disappointed.</p><p> The good news is that things are getting better, albeit slowly. The release of <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/windows-11-review-microsoft-mindful-os-200028040.html">Windows 11</a> did a lot to improve the state of HDR on PC, and more games are shipping with competent HDR modes, not just ones that increase the brightness of highlights. Unfortunately, if you want a proper HDR experience on PC, you will need to shell out for an OLED monitor.</p><h2> Gaming monitor accessories</h2><p> If you plan to spend a lot on a gaming monitor, I would recommend picking up an affordable colorimeter like the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2EuY28vZC9laG1GTGtOIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyZTQ2Yzk2NS1lZWQzLTQyYjktYTgyZS00NGRmYTQ5Zjc2ZTcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZwZk0VtLHuUQ-jTvuqQg3JX4tnsWkkxmf7gQ6mquqh_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fa.co%2Fd%2FehmFLkN" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://a.co/d/ehmFLkN">Spyder X Pro</a> alongside your new purchase. A lot of gaming monitors come uncalibrated out of the box, so their colors won&#39;t look quite right. It&#39;s possible to get a decent image with the help of online recommendations and ICC profiles you can download from websites like <em>Rtings</em> , but every panel is different and needs its own set of adjustments to look its best.</p><p> I would also recommend a monitor arm if you want to improve the ergonomics of your setup. Many gaming monitors come with subpar stands that don&#39;t offer the full range of adjustments people need to avoid bad posture. A monitor arm can help by offering a wider range of height, tilt and swivel options. Most 16:9 gaming monitors will work with VESA 100-compatible monitor arms. Vivo makes <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAV9R73BsWXkBR_5q2LAmeAp4cy2PI50S52DcVqMF-v2T&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FVIVO-Monitor-Adjustable-Articulating-STAND-V001%2Fdp%2FB00B21TLQU%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1_sspa" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/VIVO-Monitor-Adjustable-Articulating-STAND-V001/dp/B00B21TLQU/ref=sr_1_1_sspa?keywords=vivo%2Bsingle%2Bmonitor%2Barm%2Bdesk%2Bmount&amp;sr=8-1-spons&amp;sp_csd=d2lkZ2V0TmFtZT1zcF9hdGY&amp;th=1">some great affordable options</a> .</p><h2> The best gaming monitor for most people: LG 27GP850-B </h2><p><core-commerce id="d45909d8f972479b8f8aec2a3c72f182" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> For most people, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDkzTVRTVEtEP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRraC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMmU0NmM5NjUtZWVkMy00MmI5LWE4MmUtNDRkZmE0OWY3NmU3In0&amp;signature=AQAAAfuYlAEbs33Qz6-cIibhOG3iWqUmLqPWKkuXJZE4vXqr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB093MTSTKD" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B093MTSTKD?">LG 27GP850-B</a> is all the gaming monitor they need. It features an excellent 27-inch, 1440p Nano IPS panel with a native 165Hz refresh rate, and the option to overclock to 180Hz. In addition to excellent pixel response times (1m GtG, according to LG), the 27GP850-B comes with a backlight strobing feature that can further improve motion clarity for GPUs that can maintain a frame rate above 120fps. It&#39;s also FreeSync Premium and G-Sync Compatible certified.</p><p> If you can&#39;t find the 27GP850-B at your local retailers, another good option is the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDdZR1pMOFhGP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRraC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMmU0NmM5NjUtZWVkMy00MmI5LWE4MmUtNDRkZmE0OWY3NmU3In0&amp;signature=AQAAAfzKqZFR2Usr5u4EeF_Bi9-SZsyXCxWmh1jskXSv11q3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07YGZL8XF" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07YGZL8XF?">LG 27GL83A-B</a> . It&#39;s a few years old now, but offers a 144Hz refresh rate, speedy response times and it&#39;s at least $100 less than the 27GP850-B. I&#39;ve been using the Dell version of this display since mid-2021 (sadly no longer available), and can&#39;t imagine replacing it until OLED monitors become more affordable.</p><h2> A compelling budget option: ViewSonic XG2431 </h2><p><core-commerce id="40fc32d338284c4cb0d600b13ad5803f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> For a more affordable option than either LG displays mentioned above, consider the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDk3UzlTWU01P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRraC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMmU0NmM5NjUtZWVkMy00MmI5LWE4MmUtNDRkZmE0OWY3NmU3In0&amp;signature=AQAAAVXT-rptVmUOMvvPhe0_fK8LK5S6CjmTklTxlIh5WfLT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB097S9SYM5" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B097S9SYM5?">ViewSonic XG2431</a> . While its price has fluctuated in recent months, you can frequently find the XG2431 for less than $300. Coming in at 24-inches, it&#39;s on the smaller side and only features a 1080p panel. However, it offers a 240Hz refresh rate. When you combine that with its lower resolution, the XG2431 is a great option for competitive gamers on a budget.</p><h2> The best gaming monitor regardless of price: LG 27GR95QE-B </h2><p><core-commerce id="6bf06ae954584ddd914befdc85192353" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If money is no object and you enjoy a mix of immersive and competitive gaming, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJSQlc4S1JLP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRraC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMmU0NmM5NjUtZWVkMy00MmI5LWE4MmUtNDRkZmE0OWY3NmU3In0&amp;signature=AQAAAXHdB5Vg2jcVt-KvVfsFOBq9ozES9-45IKM_4zpjoK7X&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BRBW8KRK" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BRBW8KRK?">LG 27GR95QE-B</a> is the monitor to beat right now. It features a 27-inch 1440p OLED panel with a 240Hz refresh rate and sub-1ms pixel response times. In motion, the 27GR95QE-B performs a shade worse than the ASUS PG27AQM highlighted below, but, among dedicated gaming monitors, it is unmatched when it comes to HDR performance.</p><p> The 27GR95QE-B comes with all the usual issues associated with OLEDs, including the text legibility and burn-in concerns I mentioned above. It also doesn&#39;t get very bright, maxing out at about 200 nits.</p><p> A few other companies produce 27-inch OLED monitors using the same panel as the 27GR95QE-B. Most notably, there&#39;s ASUS with the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJaUkJZTFAxP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRraC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMmU0NmM5NjUtZWVkMy00MmI5LWE4MmUtNDRkZmE0OWY3NmU3In0&amp;signature=AQAAAUXc9iLD34XpM4sAAbYPBF3_OExqbNBxBY77_LDKYEaW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BZRBYLP1" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BZRBYLP1?">PG27AQDM</a> . It can get a fair bit brighter than the 27GR95QE-B, though it hasn&#39;t been out long enough for people to carry out long-term testing to determine how that affects the longevity of the panel.</p><h2> A high-end LCD option: ASUS PG27AQM </h2><p><core-commerce id="6df323ffd5434e55b861df4aee653ab6" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If the thought of spending $1,000 on an OLED monitor that could one day suffer from burn-in gives you pause, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASvqnzjxRVFFkrrx6Hezgb6H1p3ldU37H5FixaohwtHw&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FASUS-Swift-Gaming-Monitor-PG27AQN%2Fdp%2FB0BHK7LLZD" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/ASUS-Swift-Gaming-Monitor-PG27AQN/dp/B0BHK7LLZD">ASUS PG27AQN</a> is a safer high-end option. It&#39;s one of the fastest gaming monitors on the market right now, offering an impressive 360Hz refresh rate, 1ms response times and a 27-inch QHD panel. It also comes with<a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nvidia-reflex-input-lag-202333860.html">NVIDIA&#39;s Reflex module</a> , which you can use to see how your mouse, internal hardware and display contribute to your system&#39;s overall latency. However, it is expensive, coming in at $1,049, but for that price, you get one of the gaming monitors on the market right now.</p><h2> A high-end ultrawide option: Alienware AW3423DWF </h2><p><core-commerce id="5f108b64b144494d9c88a9596600f8af" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> For those set on an ultrawide monitor, one of the best options available right now is the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dell;elmt:;cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b1bb23c9-a2d4-4e4e-bfac-7a560ebe7641&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dell&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfhBqgvR4RJcYi2y_3BR4kQXUwBQD0iaQFKDOpNC_R86&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dell.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Falienware-34-curved-qd-oled-gaming-monitor-aw3423dw%2Fapd%2F210-bcye%2Fmonitors-monitor-accessories" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.dell.com/en-us/shop/alienware-34-curved-qd-oled-gaming-monitor-aw3423dw/apd/210-bcye/monitors-monitor-accessories">AW3423DWF</a> . I haven&#39;t had a chance to test it, but Engadget Senior Editor Devindra Hardawar gave Alienware&#39;s QD-OLED display a score of <a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alienware-qd-oled-gaming-monitor-ultrawide-review-140012704.html">92</a> when he reviewed it last May. At $1,299, the AW3423DWF is easily the most expensive screen on this list, but for that price you get a 21:9 gaming monitor with an up-to 175Hz refresh rate, 0.1ms response rate and HDR True Black 400 performance. The only thing it&#39;s missing is an HDMI 2.1 port.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-monitor-140008940.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-monitor-140008940.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 2e46c965-eed3-42b9-a82e-44dfa49f76e7</guid><dc:creator> Igor Bonifacic</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 31 Aug 2023 14:00:08 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693491401</ingested><modified> 2023-08-31T14:16:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Igor Bonifacic]]></category><media:content height="992" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/dc829e30-4808-11ee-bd6f-5e82f8cab71d" width="1432"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></med